<body>
  <h1>DivineChat Support</h1>
  <p>Welcome to the support page for DivineChat — an app that allows you to explore scripture and reflect through guided conversations with biblical figures.</p>

  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="faq">
    <div class="question">What is DivineChat?</div>
    <div>DivineChat is an educational app that simulates conversations with biblical figures using AI. It's designed to help users reflect on scripture, ask questions, and engage with biblical history in a more personal way.</div>

    <div class="question">Does DivineChat give religious or pastoral advice?</div>
    <div>No. The app is for educational and spiritual reflection purposes only. It does not replace pastoral counseling, therapy, or church guidance.</div>

    <div class="question">Is my data stored or shared?</div>
    <div>No. Conversations are processed securely via a backend server and are not stored or used for any external purpose. No account or personal information is required.</div>

    <div class="question">Can I talk to any figure in the Bible?</div>
    <div>Currently, the app supports a curated list of biblical figures such as Jesus, Moses, Ruth, Paul, and others. More may be added in future updates.</div>

    <div class="question">Do I need an internet connection?</div>
    <div>Yes. DivineChat requires internet access to communicate with the AI backend and provide real-time responses.</div>
  </div>

